results.subscriptionSummary:
NEWCASTLE officials said second-rower Alex McKinnon had movement in his limbs after he was the victim of a horror tackle at AAMI Park. 

Play was held up for about five minutes when the second-rower was fitted with a neck brace after his head doubled under him when heavily dumped in a tackle by Melbourne’s Kenny Bromwich, Jesse Bromwich and Jordan McLean in the Storm’s 28-20 win.
